ADAPTUM IPv10 is released under a Dual Licensing Model. You may choose the license that best fits your use case:

License Type: AGPLv3
Who It's For: Individuals, researchers, OSS projects, teams <= 10 people
Cost: Free
Source Code Disclosure: Required (if modified)

License Type: Commercial License
Who It's For: Organizations > 10 employees/users
Cost: Paid
Source Code Disclosure: Not required


1. OPEN SOURCE LICENSE — GNU AGPLv3

For individuals, non-commercial use, academic research, and teams with 10 or fewer members, ADAPTUM IPv10 is freely available under the GNU Affero General Public License v3.0 (AGPLv3).

Key Requirements:
- You must disclose source code when distributing modified versions.
- If you run modified software as a network service, you must make the source code available to users.
- Changes must be licensed under the same AGPLv3 terms.

Full text: https://www.gnu.org/licenses/agpl-3.0.txt


2. COMMERCIAL LICENSE — ADAPTUM IPv10 COMMERCIAL LICENSE

This license applies to organizations and enterprises that:
- Have more than 10 employees or concurrent users
- Cannot or do not wish to comply with AGPLv3's source code disclosure requirements
- Intend to use ADAPTUM IPv10 in proprietary, closed-source, or internal-only environments

Terms & Conditions

2.1 Paid License
This license requires a one-time or subscription fee based on:
- Number of employees (>= 11)
- Number of concurrent users
- Deployment scale

2.2 No Source Code Disclosure
Unlike AGPLv3, you are NOT required to disclose your modified source code to the public.

2.3 Closed Distribution Rights
You have the full right to:
- Use ADAPTUM IPv10 in proprietary systems
- Modify the code privately
- Distribute binaries without accompanying source
- Integrate into commercial products

2.4 No Warranty
This software is provided "AS IS" without warranties of any kind.

2.5 Redistribution
You may not sublicense or distribute the software under terms more restrictive than this Commercial License without written permission.


